revision.text:
'''Bodhimaṇḍala''' is a term in [[Buddhism]] that means "circle of [[Bodhi|awakening]]." Although spelled similarly, a bodhimaṇḍala is not synonymous with a ''[[bodhimaṇḍa]]'', which is a [[bodhisattva]]'s seat of awakening.<ref>Thurman, Robert. ''The Holy Teaching of Vimalakīrti: A Mahāyāna Scripture.'' 1992. p. 120</ref>

