[[File:Dwarbasini.jpeg|thumb|right]] '''Dwarbasini''' ("দ্বারবাসিনী") is a [[Shakti]] goddess. She is the form of goddess [[Durga]]. The Dwarbasini temple is situated on the bank of [[Dwarka River]] and at the end of [[Deucha]]-Boliharpur road.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bristii.wapka.mobi/site_39.xhtml |title=DWARBASINI TEMPLE |first=|last=}}</ref> Here [[Dwarka River]] is flowing twords north, and according to [[tantra]] '''Dwarbasini''' is a [[shakti]]pith.
==Etymology== From a folk story we get the name of 'Raja Umacharan Roy'. He was a great devotee of the goddess 'Dwarbasini' ani had died by [[Santhal people|Santhal]]s at [[Santhal rebellion]]. He had donated lands to allocate flowers, woods, rices, sweets, milk etc at the village [[chondrapur]]([[Chondrapur|চন্দ্রপুর]])<ref>folk story</ref> <gallery> File:Dwarbasini idol1.jpeg|dwarbasini stone idol File:Dwarbasini vairav.png|thumb|Vairob of dwarbasini </gallery> .
==Origins== Goddess Dwarbasini is a stone idol with no image. She here is goddess [[Durga]] with [[Laxmi]], [[Saraswati]], [[Kartikeya|Kartik]], and [[Ganesha]]. This temple was built near about 30 years ago. Before this temple was made, Dwarbasini was covered with the [[bamboo]] umbrella, made by [[Santhal people|Santhal]]s.<ref>Subrata Majumdar, maternal relation with Dwarbasini priest family</ref>
==History == Dwarbasini is a 'sini' goddess like palashbasini, duarsini etc. Probably she was worshiped by [[Santhals]], and pahria [[Mal (caste)|Mal]]s.<ref>birbhumer katha</ref>
==Etymology== From a folk story we have the name of 'Raja Umacharan Roy'. He was a great devotee of goddess 'Dwarbasini'. He had no son. So he had adopted a son who was the forefather of the '[[Banerjee|Bondopadhaya]]' priest family. At the time of [[Santhal rebellion|The santhal Rebellion]] Umacharan had killed by [[Santhal people|santhal]]s.<ref>folk story and 'kursinama' of priest family</ref>
