r el-Machreq Publishers}}</ref>
==Roman temple== There are the ruins of a [[Roman temple]] in the village that are included in a group of [[Temples of the Beqaa Valley]].<ref name="Keel1997">{{cite book|author=Othmar Keel|title=The Symbolism of the Biblical World: Ancient Near Eastern Iconography and the Book of Psalms|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Fy4B1iMg33YC&pg=PA159|accessdate=27 October 2012|year=1997|publisher=Eisenbrauns|isbn=978-1-57506-014-9|pages=159–}}</ref> The temple foundations are made of gigantic blocks of stone, upon which sit the remains of a [[podium]]. The podium has a long inscription written on it that is now almost impossible to read.<ref name="Taylor1967"/>
